<HEAD>Four Children Die in Early Morning Fire at Foster Home</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A predawn arson fire in a foster home killed four children and injured 12 other people, with two adults and four children hospitalized in critical condition, fire officials said. The fire was the work of an arsonist, said fire Lt. <PERSON> Jack </PERSON> <PERSON> Christmas </PERSON>, who added that smoke detectors were found in the house but nothing indicated they had been installed. He would not elaborate. Neighbors said they woke up shortly before 3 a.m. smelling smoke and hearing the cries of children. `` I heard the kids and they were screaming, ` Help me! Help me!' It was horrible,'' said <PERSON> Gloria </PERSON> <PERSON> Page </PERSON>, who lives next door. When firefighters arrived at the three-story, stone-and-frame house, they found heavy fire in the first floor and people trapped upstairs. Neighbor <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Hart </PERSON> said he woke up hearing a car in the street honking its horn. `` Then I looked out the window and I saw all this fire raging in the front of the house,'' he said. <PERSON> Hart </PERSON> said he ran behind the house and found three or four children who had jumped from second - and third-story windows He said he looked up and saw `` five or six more'' standing at the windows. `` They were crying and shaking and screaming,'' he said. <PERSON> Hart </PERSON> said he tried to build a platform out of wood so the children could have a shorter distance to jump. `` They would n't jump on it, so I told them to jump and I'd catch them. So they jumped and I tried to catch them or break their fall,'' <PERSON> Hart </PERSON> said. The fire was under control by 3:20 a.m., firefighters said. Seventeen people lived in the house, firefighters said. The children who died were found on the second floor. Police identified the dead children as <PERSON> Keith </PERSON> <PERSON> Moye </PERSON>, 7, and his brother, <PERSON> Preston </PERSON> <PERSON> Moye </PERSON>, 5; <PERSON> Anwar </PERSON> <PERSON> Hartwell </PERSON>, 9, and <PERSO