le who took in so many children because they had plenty of room in their spacious house. The Artises had been foster parents since 1972, according to <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Olanoff </PERSON> of the city's <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Human </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>. State law prohibits more than six children in a foster home, but police counted 11 children living among the 17 residents of the house when the fire broke out. <PERSON> Olanoff </PERSON> said the department granted the Artises a waiver to care for eight children about a year ago.
