<FIRST>r a PM-KnotNews-Steps     08-31 0076</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Knot News-Steps,0080</SECOND>
<HEAD>With Knot News</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Here are five steps involved in tying the Shelby knot. 1. Start with the tie seamside out, with the wide end under the narrow end. 2. Loop the wide end over and under the narrow end. 3. Tighten to take up slack. 4. Take wide end across to the right and under the neck loop. 5. Thread wide end down through the knot and tighten.
