<HEAD>Racial Tension High, Some Violence After Funeral Services for Vineland
Man</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MELANIE BURNEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEWFIELD, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 As racial tension and violence continued over the fatal shooting of a black man by police, about 200 people gathered for the victim's funeral and heard a prayer he wrote pleading for a better life. Community leaders in <LOCATION> Vineland </LOCATION> had hoped the violence that followed Sunday night's shooting had subsided, but unrest continued late Wednesday and four more people were arrested. Hour earlier, mourners packed into <ORGANIZATION> Truth </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Baptist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> in the nearby town of <LOCATION> Newfield </LOCATION> for the two-hour ceremony and listened to a reading of the prayer written by <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Williams </PERSON> shortly before his death. He called it `` A Letter to the Lord.'' `` My Father, bless me so I can bless my family and do better,'' the 26-year-old <PERSON> Williams </PERSON> wrote. `` Help.'' Before the service, <LOCATION> Vineland </LOCATION> Mayor <PERSON> Harry </PERSON> <PERSON> Curley </PERSON> met with community leaders to defuse the unrest. He said an eight-member special task force was formed to find a way to restore calm in the southern <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> city. `` We're hoping this will be the first step,'' <PERSON> Curley </PERSON> said. `` We're hoping that we can be assured there wo n't be any more outbreaks.'' <PERSON> Curley </PERSON> said 32 people have been arrested since Monday night, when some 200 people threw rocks and bottles at stores lining the city's main drag In Wednesday's violence, a WPVI-TV news crew from <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION> was attacked by youths as they interviewed people in downtown <LOCATION> Vineland </LOCATION>, where the rioting and looting first broke out Monday, said city spokesman <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Tofanelli </PERSON>. Reporter <PERSON> Dann </PERSON> <PERSON> Cuellar </PERSON> was listed in stable condition at <ORGANIZATION> Newcomb </ORGANIZ