<HEAD>Israeli Dies of Firebomb Wounds, Sharon Calls for Killing Masked
Youths</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ALLYN FISHER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An Israeli tax collector died today of injuries suffered in a firebomb attack by Palestinian assailants in the occupied <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION>, a hospital spokeswoman said. Industry Minister <PERSON> Ariel </PERSON> <PERSON> Sharon </PERSON>, meanwhile, suggested <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> consider legalizing the killing of masked Palestinians without checking whether they are armed. He said the masked youths are the ringleaders behind slayings in the 20-month-old uprising. In another development, <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> reports said a Palestinian teen-ager died of wounds suffered in a clash four days ago with soldiers in the occupied <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>. In the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> city of <LOCATION> Nablus </LOCATION>, the body of a 28-year-old Palestinian was found in a pushcart with stab wounds, <ORGANIZATION> Israel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> radio </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> reports said. The man, whose name was not given, was believed to have been slain as a suspected collaborator with the Israeli authorities, raising the number of such Arab deaths in the uprising to 101. The army said it was investigating the circumstances of the slaying. An army spokesman said the military was investigating a possible link between a stoning attack in the <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> two weeks ago and the death of a reservist soldier at his home on Wednesday. In northern <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, a Soviet-made <LOCATION> Katyusha </LOCATION> rocket fired from southern <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> slammed into a home on Wednesday night, breaking most of its windows but causing no injury, the army said. Northern Commander Gen. <PERSON> Yossi </PERSON> <PERSON> Peled </PERSON> said the attack appeared to be the work of the pro-Iranian Shiite Moslem movement <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION>, or Party of God. He said <LOCATION> Israel </LO