<HEAD>Game Show Host Bob Barker Sued By Humane Association</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ANNE M. PETERSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Game show host and animal rights crusader <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Barker </PERSON> has been slapped with a $ 10 million libel lawsuit by the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Humane </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> and its <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION> director. The action, filed in Superior Court Wednesday, contends <PERSON> Barker </PERSON> and other animal rights organizations conducted a two-year campaign to ruin the reputation of the association and its regional director <PERSON> Betty </PERSON> <PERSON> Denny </PERSON> <PERSON> Smith </PERSON>. The lawsuit claims <PERSON> Barker </PERSON> falsely stated on radio shows that the association allowed muzzling of two dogs and approved a fight between the animals on the film `` The Tender,'' which would have been illegal. <PERSON> Barker </PERSON> also claimed the association lied on its reports of an investigation of cruelty against chimpanzees during production of the film `` Project X,'' the lawsuit says. <PERSON> Barker </PERSON> denied the allegations. `` If this suit results in the <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> public becoming more aware of the extent of animal cruelty in entertainment then the suit will have served a very valuable purpose and it will be well worth the money and the time it costs me,'' he said. The lawsuit accuses <PERSON> Barker </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Activists </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Animal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rights </ORGANIZATION> and its executive director, <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Burnet </PERSON>, of libel, slander, trade libel, interference with prospective business relations, conspiracy and false-light invasion of privacy, association attorney <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> <PERSON> Langberg </PERSON> said. `` No one is saying Mr. <PERSON> Barker </PERSON> is n't an animal rights activist,'' <PERSON> Langb