<HEAD>Execution Ordered for Couple Convicted of Abduction and Torture</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN BERNARDINO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A woman who said she was brutalized into helping her boyfriend in a rape-murder was sentenced to death by a judge who said he believed she `` was in this thing up to the hilt.'' <PERSON> Cynthia </PERSON> <PERSON> Lynn </PERSON> <PERSON> Coffman </PERSON>, 27, on Wednesday became the first woman to be sentenced to death in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> since capital punishment was reinstated in 1977. Superior Court Judge <PERSON> Don </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Turner </PERSON> sentenced both her and her former lover, <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Gregory </PERSON> <PERSON> Marlow </PERSON>, 33, to death for the Nov. 7, 1986, slaying of <PERSON> Corinna </PERSON> <PERSON> Novis </PERSON>, 20. They still face charges in the death of another young woman whose body was found five days later. Ms. <PERSON> Coffman </PERSON> wiped away tears when the sentence was pronounced. `` I'm sorry for what happened and I am ashamed that I let it happen,'' she told <PERSON> Turner </PERSON>. Ms. <PERSON> Coffman </PERSON> testified she was brutalized and forced to commit the crimes, but the judge upheld the jury's recommendation, saying Ms. <PERSON> Coffman </PERSON> `` was in this thing up to the hilt and enjoyed it up to the last minute.'' `` They were equal partners in this thing all the way down the line,'' <PERSON> Chip </PERSON> <PERSON> Haight </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bernardino </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> deputy district attorney, said after Wednesday's sentencing. `` I did n't buy her domination story one bit.'' Ms. <PERSON> Coffman </PERSON> testified that <PERSON> Marlow </PERSON> raped her, beat her and cut off all her hair. She said he once told her, `` I am the devil, and I own you.'' Ms. <PERSON> Coffman </PERSON>, who has a 9-year-old son, will be imprisoned at the Correctional Institution for Women at <LOCATION> Frontera </LOCATION>. If appeals that are expected to take several years fail, she will be executed in the gas chamber. One woman has been executed in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> since capital punishment was reinstated by the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in 1977. <PERSON> Velma </PERSON> <PERSON> Barfield </PERSON>, 52, was put to death in <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION> in 1984 for poisoning her boyfriend. The last woman executed in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> was 58-year-old convicted killer <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> Ann </PERSON> <PERSON> Duncan </PERSON> in 1962. Ms. <PERSON> Novis </PERSON> was raped, tortured and killed after she offered to give Ms. <PERSON> Coffman </PERSON> and <PERSON> Marlow </PERSON> a ride near a shopping mall in <LOCATION> Redlands </LOCATION>. Ms. <PERSON> Coffman </PERSON> said she thought she and her boyfriend were only going to kidnap and rob the woman. The judge said it was clear the two planned murder. `` One of the reasons she was fascinated with Mr. <PERSON> Marlow </PERSON> and made him her man is that he had the strength to do things she could not do,'' <PERSON> Turner </PERSON> said.
