<HEAD>With AM-Lebanon</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> has remained silent this week on the possibility of a trip by Pope <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> II </PERSON> to <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>, while apparently keeping up diplomatic efforts to arrange such a mission. <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> spokesman <PERSON> Joaquin </PERSON> <PERSON> Navarro </PERSON> told reporters on Aug. 25 that `` different practical possibilities are being studied so that this desire of the pope can be carried out'' and contacts were under way `` on different levels.'' Since then, <PERSON> Navarro </PERSON> and other <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> officials have declined to elaborate on the statement. The pontiff first said Aug. 15 that he wanted to go to <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> to pray for peace there. But several obstacles have cropped up to a possible papal trip, including a recommendation by the pro-Iranian leader of <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>'s fundamentalist Sunni Moslems that the pontiff be kidnapped A previously unknown Islamic organization also threatened in <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION> Monday to kill <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> if he visited <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> has frequently expressed anguish in recent weeks about the six-month battle between Christian troops and Syrian-led forces including Lebanese Moslems. The fighting has claimed more than 810 lives. On Wednesday, during his weekly general audience, the pontiff appealed once again for prayers for peace in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> media have also been quiet on a possible papal peace mission since Sunday, when the director of the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> daily <PERSON> L'Osservatore </PERSON> <PERSON> Romano </PERSON> defended such a trip in a front-page commentary. `` Certainly, those who carry out politics only with the criteria of craftiness and slyness ca n't understand th