<HEAD>New Form Of Speed Dubbed `Ice' is `Real Horror Story'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Ice, a potent new form of the drug known as speed with a high that lasts 12 to 24 hours, is on the streets in <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION> and is threatening to invade major <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION> ports. `` This is a real horror story,'' <ORGANIZATION> Honolulu </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Police </ORGANIZATION> Captain <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> Lau </PERSON> told the <ORGANIZATION> San </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Francisco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chronicle </ORGANIZATION> on Thursday. Ice, a colorless and odorless form of the stimulant methamphetamine, is smoked much like crack, the highly addictive rock form of cocaine. But unlike a crack high, which lasts less than half an hour, a few puffs of ice can keep the user high all day. Ice has been found at all levels of society in <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION>, authorities said. `` It's a nightmare here, and there is still only a glimmer of understanding of its long-term effects,'' said <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Attorney <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Bent </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Honolulu </LOCATION>. `` Only now are we learning that its high is many times more potent and longer than crack, that its low is deep, morbid and entrenched, and that its addiction is at least as great as crack and possibly far greater.'' Most of the ice in <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION> appears to be coming from <LOCATION> Asia </LOCATION>. `` Normally, we are not on the cutting edge of something like this,'' said Major <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Carvalho </PERSON> of the <LOCATION> Honolulu </LOCATION> police narcotics squad. `` Drugs usually come here from the mainland heading west; but this drug is coming from the opposite direction _ the <LOCATION> Far </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>. `` Its couriers are not <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> gang members like the Crips and the Bloods, but gang members from the <LOCATION> Philippines </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> who are just as deadly. We have become their test tube for smokable crystal meth.'' Ice costs two to three times the current price of crack cocaine, <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION> police said. While crack might cost $ 2,000 a pound, ice is $ 4,000 to $ 6,000 for the same amount.
