<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> has slotted the new <PERSON> Mel </PERSON> <PERSON> Brooks </PERSON> comedy `` The <ORGANIZATION> Nutt </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION>'' after the broad comedy `` Night Court,'' which by comparison looks like a candidate for `` Masterpiece Theatre.'' The humor in the preliminary pilot for `` <ORGANIZATION> Nutt </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION>,'' which will undergo some changes before its premiere, ranged from broad _ the hotel boa constrictor is dispatched to make quick work of a rat _ to slapstick _ `` Suing <PERSON> Sadie </PERSON>'' attempting to fall down the stairs. <PERSON> Cloris </PERSON> <PERSON> Leachman </PERSON>, equipped with fake bosoms and derriere, is the oversexed head of housekeeping for the large and wacky <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> hotel. <PERSON> Harvey </PERSON> <PERSON> Korman </PERSON> is the foppish hotel manager. In the pilot, the fate of the hotel hangs in the balance as a <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> tycoon plots to buy it and the heir to the hotel fortune -LRB- <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> McNamara </PERSON> -RRB- is a party boy extraordinaire, ill-prepared to handle the responsibility. `` I'm a ne'er - do-well,'' he `` The only thing I do well is ne'er.'' <PERSON> Brooks </PERSON> is executive producer with <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> Spencer </PERSON>, a kind of protege of <PERSON> Brooks </PERSON> who created the wacky `` Sledge Hammer!'' of a couple seasons ago. Viewers who are either over-medicated or underage might find `` The Nutt House'' amusing. For the rest of us, cancel our reservations.
