</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Federal disclosure rules taking effect today will make it easier to shop for a credit card, fostering competition that could lower interest rates for the nation's 107 million cardholders. The regulations require credit card issuers to disclose the interest rate, monthly fee, grace period and other terms in a chart on the application used to sign up customers. Until now, companies have not had to disclose a card's costs until it arrived in the mail, under federal regulations. However, a dozen states have their own disclosure rules.
</TEXT>
