<HEAD>Exxon Appoints Environmentalist To Board</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JULIA C. MARTINEZ</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The scientist appointed to help oversee <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s future environmental policies and practices calls the <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION> oil spill a `` terrible disaster.'' <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Steele </PERSON> on Wednesday was named a director of the nation's largest oil company The appointment follows <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION>'s promise earlier this year to large shareholders to appoint a director with interest and expertise in the environment in the wake of the company's <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION> oil spill. Major shareholders and some environmentalists said they approved of the marine scientist. But other environmental groups were not pleased by the choice. <PERSON> Steele </PERSON>, 62, is president of and a senior scientist at the Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution in <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION>. In addition to his seat on the board of directors he will serve on the board's newly formed public issues committee, which monitors the company's environmental policies `` I'm confident his presence on the board will increase <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION>'s sensitivity to environmental concerns,'' said <PERSON> Gray </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>, controller of the <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Employee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Retirement </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> System </ORGANIZATION>, the largest individual <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> public pension fund, which owns <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> stock `` Protecting the environment is both good public policy and good business,'' said <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>, who is also co-chairman of the <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> D.C.-based </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institutional </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Investo