<HEAD>Allstate Insurance Introduces Discount for Anti-lock Brake Systems</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CHARLES J. GANS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Drivers of cars equipped with anti-lock brakes could soon be getting a break on their auto insurance rates. In a move that could set a precedent for other major insurance companies, <ORGANIZATION> Allstate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Insurance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> announced Wednesday it is offering a 10 percent discount on three major auto-policy coverages for cars with anti-lock brakes. `` This discount, in effect, is the first of its kind for a major carrier,'' said <PERSON> Greg </PERSON> <PERSON> Rossiter </PERSON>, a spokesman for the company, based in the <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> suburb of <LOCATION> Northbrook </LOCATION>. The only other <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> insurance company currently offering an anti-lock brake system discount is <ORGANIZATION> USAA </ORGANIZATION>, of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Antonio </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, a firm which provides insurance to military personnel and their dependents, <PERSON> Rossiter </PERSON> said. Anti-lock brakes use an on-board computer to control wheel speed during braking, allowing faster and safer stops without skidding or loss of steering control. `` There's no question that the anti-lock brake system provides a remarkable amount of braking protection that is not available in regular brake systems,'' <PERSON> Rossiter </PERSON> said. <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Geen </PERSON>, senior vice-president of <ORGANIZATION> CCC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Information </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a Chicago-based firm that evaluates car losses for the insurance industry, said he also has found that anti-lock brakes are effective. `` It's certainly been proven that the anti-lock brake system works very well and more manufacturers are offering it.'' <PERSON> Geen </PERSON> said he expected other insurance companies to follow <ORGANIZATION> Allstate </ORGANIZATION>'s example in offering the anti-lock brake discount. <PERSON> Geen </PERSON> said there are few cars on the road with anti-lock brakes, but they should be available as an optional or standard feature on more 1990 model cars. The anti-lock system was introduced about six years ago, and until recently has only been available on luxury cars. It is now being offered as an option on more moderately priced autos, but no statistics are available as to how many cars now on the road in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> have anti-lock brakes, <PERSON> Rossiter </PERSON> said. The new discount offered by <ORGANIZATION> Allstate </ORGANIZATION>, a subsidiary of <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Roebuck </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, covers cars equipped with four-wheel anti-lock brake systems. It provides for 10 percent off three coverages that are part of an auto policy _ bodily injury, property damage liability and collision.
