be the first agency to use AT & amp; T's portion of the new data network services. <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T said the <ORGANIZATION> HFCA </ORGANIZATION> contract was worth $ 100 million. Existing switched voice communications at some federal agencies will begin to be changed over to FTS2000 in October. <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T will serve such agencies as <ORGANIZATION> HHS </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agriculture </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aeronautics </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Space </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION>. <LOCATION> US </LOCATION> Sprint will serve such agencies as the Department of Veterans Affairs, the <ORGANIZATION> GSA </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>.
